From d4f8f2f3e4ddab0c72d1374ffb4e90f62a62a7c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hologram OS2 <ilya@uor.foundation>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 09:27:44 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat(archive,exec): WeightIndex section + range-resolver lazy
 weight loading (ADR-0101 Stage 2)

Stream a .holo model as kappa-addressable, demand-paged weight blocks instead of
decoding the whole Weights section into a second in-RAM WeightStore.

- format: new optional SectionKind::WeightIndex (additive, backward-compatible).
- writer: emit the Weights payload (unchanged) AND a WeightIndex in one pass, so
  each index entry locates a body within the Weights payload.
- weight_index: WeightIndex decode + LazyWeightStore over a RangeResolver
  (SliceResolver for a resident archive; a custom resolver for a kappa-store/file
  fetch = true demand-paging). Every fetched body is re-derived against its
  fingerprint before return (Law L5).
- loader: LoadedPlan::section_ref to anchor index offsets to absolute positions.
- exec/session: prefer the lazy path (sizing from the index, one body resident at
  a time, L5-verified); fall back to the eager WeightStore for index-less archives.

Eliminates the all-bodies HashMap at load (a full second copy of the weight set);
sizing no longer reads weight bytes. Backward-compatible: index-less .holo still load.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
